  "instructions": [
    "Rinse the sugar snap peas and pat dry.",
    "Heat 1 tbsp coconut oil in a small saucepan over medium heat.",
    "Add minced garlic and saut\u00e9 until fragrant, about 30 seconds.",
    "Stir in tamarind paste, honey, cumin, paprika, salt, and pepper; cook for 1 minute.",
    "Add the snap peas and toasted pine nuts, tossing to coat.",
    "Warm the mixture for 2 minutes, keeping the peas crisp.",
    "Remove from heat and stir in almond butter, lemon juice, and the remaining 1 tbsp coconut oil until a glossy dressing forms.",
    "Fold in the cooked chickpeas for extra protein.",
    "Taste and adjust seasoning if needed.",
    "Serve immediately as a refreshing lunch or snack."
